					<p>Living today in the U.S. is more expensive than ever. Even the price of stamps has gone up 204 percent from 1980 to today.</p><p>In this video, Entrepreneur Network partner and financial expert <a>Patrick Bet-David</a> says to a crowd gathered on his 30-day speaking tour that dramatic increase would be perfectly OK -- as long as an increase in average income was just as dramatic. But it's not. </p><p>"How am I supposed to pay for my utilities, car payment, birthdays, weddings -- all of this stuff, how am I supposed to do it?" he says. "And how do you afford to have three kids?"</p><p>Click play to get Bet-David's thoughts on how entrepreneurship is the only solution to inflation. Get more highlights from his <a>Official Startup Entrepreneur Tour here. </a></p><p><em>Watch more YouTube videos from <a>Bet-David on his channel.</a></em></p><p></p><p><a><em>Entrepreneur Network</em></a> <em>is a </em><a><em>premium video network</em></a><em> providing entertainment, education and inspiration from successful entrepreneurs and thought leaders. We provide expertise and opportunities to accelerate brand growth and effectively monetize video and audio content distributed across all digital platforms for the business genre.</em></p><p><em>EN is partnered with hundreds of top </em><a><em>YouTube channels</em></a><em> in the business vertical and provides partners with distribution on </em><a><em>Entrepreneur.com</em></a><em> as well as our apps on </em><a><em>Amazon Fire</em></a><em>, </em><a><em>Roku</em></a><em> and </em><a><em>Apple TV</em></a><em>.</em></p><p></p>				
				
